Today marks 7 years since my first tv role. So much has happened since then.  I’m so grateful to be on the journey that I’m on, to have the people that I have by my side, the experiences that I’ve had. I have traveled the world and I’ve made really great friends while pursuing this career. I’ve challenged myself, I’ve failed, I’ve surprised myself, I’ve grown and I have learned so much. Needless to say,this was just amazing. Thank you to @kalpenn and @tlabine and @konnartist for the amazing experience. Thank you for the camaraderie. Thank you for always being a very positive part of this journey… a very momentous part of my life. #Deadbeat #Actor #Grateful

I am grateful for everything in my life…. My family, friends, blessings, struggles, my failures and my successes. I’m grateful for everything that that lead me to this moment right here. This life is so unpredictable and insanely short. Smile when you can. Cry when you need to. Laugh as loud as possible. Don’t hold anything in. I promise you this, that pain, that struggle, that failure… it’s all gonna make you the best version of yourself. You may not see it now, but it will. 

📸: @robert.vazquez.94009841

Looking back on pivotal moments in my career and this one in particular stands out almost immediately. This is by far my favorite experience as an actor. The cast and crew of @therighteousgemstones were just so welcoming and so damn talented. To have grown up watching these men and then I suddenly get to work with them was…just WOW! To share art and new experiences with them… it was a dream come true. The conversations behind the camera with the great @ericrobertsactor and #JohnGoodman were unforgettable. I can’t forget @itslizziemears, thank you so much for being an awesome scene partner. You were the perfect one for the job. Killed it! Thank you to #DavidGordonGreen for being so hands on and allowing me to really tap into the character. Thank you for trusting me as an actor. The stunt team was just the bees knees! Never felt more comfortable punching a couple of guys! Lol

.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

Because it’s #FlashbackFriday here’s a clip of a show that I had the absolute honor to be a part of.  I didn’t realize how much it meant to me to be involved in a project with an all Latin cast. It was something I needed. It was something that was missing from my career. The love felt real. The representation of so many countries in such a positive way was so amazing. To see Latinos be heroes, parents, role models.. it touched me in a place deep in my heart. To have played a character that people looked up to was so wonderful. It’s something that I’ll always cherish something I’ll never forget. 

.

Happy birthday dad! I think about you every day! I’m grateful for everything and I mean EVERYTHING! The ups, the downs, the lessons, the wisdom, the discipline, the laughs, the cries and everything else in between. Thank you for being one of the greatest to have ever done it. I love you so much pops! You are and will always be in my heart. I will forever use you as the blueprint for my life and my future. Thank you for showing us unconditional love. Thank you for sacrificing your time, mind, body and heart for your children. Thank you dad!!!! Today, I celebrate that amazing man that is you! I love you dad, for ever and ever! 

.

2023 was a year filled with family, friends, art, exploration, struggle, growth and an abundance of love. It was a year of travel, chances taken, failures and successes. I’m grateful for all of it. So glad I had the opportunities I’ve had. Now, to focus on this year. This year WILL be the year!!! May you go after what you want. May you fail and fail again. When you do, just get up and keep going. Work harder and harder. Here’s to growth. Here’s to progress. Here’s to success. Here’s to #2024. Happy new year! 

.
